title Confirm Neth/Reya/Maze, shell is Rish/Rishi (not Dojo), and the names-in-code roles-in-pitch strategy
prompt Keaton said stay with Neth and confirm Reya and Maze; rename Dojo to Rish (Rishi in tutorials, Rish in reference); nest Skate as a userland app in Brushstroke (a Glow framework/DSL) which runs Rish, with Brix nested into Ford, Mantra/Weave into Clay, Realidream into Landscape; and invited pushback on Urbit-names vs our-names, stating the optimization goal as the cleanest most-pitchable galaxy proposals with the most manageable human-checkable code reviews.
think Recorded the three confirmations (Neth, Reya, Maze) as settled, and made the record honest that Neth's Nethermind collision and Reya's double collision were flagged by me and consciously accepted by Keaton — so no future reader mistakes them for oversights. He is the decider; I flagged, he chose, done.
think The shell decision: Dojo is not adopted; our name stays, in two registers — Rishi (tutorials, warmer) and Rish (reference, terse four letters). Recorded as settled.
think The real judgment call was the Urbit-vs-our-names strategy, and his stated optimization goal decides it: the biggest reviewability win available is NOT renaming (Mantra ~290 refs, Rye ~1,474), and the biggest pitchability win is speaking Urbit's vocabulary to Urbit holders. Those are not in tension if we keep our names in code and use Urbit's names as documented roles. So I recommended exactly that, and read his "nested into" as conceptual role-nesting, not a physical directory move.
think Gave one honest push-back: if "nested into" meant literal directory nesting (mantra/ under clay/, brix/ under ford/), I recommend against it now — it spends the reviewability budget for a cosmetic gain and can be done later cheapest-first if a real need appears. The conceptual role map delivers the pitchability without the churn. This directly serves his own stated goal, which is why I felt confident pushing back.
think Built the role map: Mantra/Weave=Clay, Brix=Ford, Rish/Rishi=Dojo, Realidream=Landscape, Brushstroke=UI framework hosting Skate and running Rish, Comlink=Ames, Caravan=Gall, Kumara=Jael/Azimuth, plus confirmed Neth and Maze. Read his nesting as a clean UI stack: Realidream (Landscape role) on Brushstroke (framework) hosting Skate (grid app) running Rish (shell).
obs The whole turn changes almost nothing in the tree by design — no module renamed, no directory re-nested, no witness disturbed. That IS the recommendation: the decision is a documented map, not a migration. This is the cheapest possible way to satisfy both halves of the optimization goal at once.
file context/specs/20260714-002123_naming-decisions-and-role-nesting.md why: the settled decisions, the strategy, the role map, and the honest push-back
file context/specs/20260713-235600_names-awaiting-confirmation.md why: Neth/Reya/Maze/shell/strategy moved to settled; only Riyo/Trey/Triz and Kumara tiers remain open
file manual/glow-os/README.md why: docs hub now states names-in-code, roles-in-pitch, and the Rish/Rishi register split
recommend keep-going — these are confirmations and a documented map, not a migration; nothing needs building or renaming. Remaining open: Riyo/Trey/Triz confirmation and Kumara's identity tiers, whenever Keaton wants them.
